    "In this assignment we are investigating how different portfolio weights can lead to statistical errors based on the paper of @987c7289-8939-3a32-96f2-3d9b692dffee and @BRANDT2010269. \n",
    "The method to test this is to check how our portfolio weights deviate from the optimal in a single factor model market model which treats the calibrated parameters as the true values. we use this equation for portfolio weights:\n",
    "$$\n",
    "\\hat{\\omega}(\\bar{\\mu}) = \\arg\\min_{\\omega} \\, \\omega' \\hat{\\Sigma} \\omega \n",
    "\\quad \\text{s.t.} \\quad \\omega'\\iota = 1 \n",
    "\\quad \\text{and} \\quad \\omega'\\hat{\\mu} \\geq \\bar{\\mu}\n",
    "$$\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
