    "We now use the data to calculate these:\n",
    "Let $r_{m,t}$ be the monthly return and $r_{f,t}$ the risk-free rate.\n",
    "\n",
    "**1. Monthly Excess Return**\n",
    "$$\\tilde{r}_{m,t} = r_{m,t} - r_{f,t}$$\n",
    "\n",
    "**2. Monthly Mean Excess Return**\n",
    "$$\\hat{\\mu}_m = \\frac{1}{T} \\sum_{t=1}^{T} \\tilde{r}_{m,t}$$\n",
    "\n",
    "**3. Monthly Variance**\n",
    "$$\\hat{\\sigma}_m^2 = \\frac{1}{T-1} \\sum_{t=1}^{T} \\left(\\tilde{r}_{m,t} - \\hat{\\mu}_m\\right)^2$$\n",
    "\n",
    "**4. Annualized Mean Excess Return**\n",
    "$$\\hat{\\mu}_{m,\\text{ann}} = 12 \\times \\hat{\\mu}_m$$\n",
    "\n",
    "**5. Annualized Variance**\n",
    "$$\\hat{\\sigma}_{m,\\text{ann}}^2 = 12 \\times \\hat{\\sigma}_m^2$$"
   ]
